 again the four German refugees were discussing passport problems, and presently a fifth entered and cheerfully said: “Bonjour, Monsieur Weiss, bonjour, Monsieur Meyer.” To my questions, Shishkov replied, rather absently and as it were reluctantly, that the idea of his journal had been found unrealizable, and that he had stopped thinking about it.

